@mariohct

MU-photos
=========

Picture frame 

LINUX configurations
====================
- add run2.sh to be loaded by .profile
- change inittab for automatic login on user pi
  1:2345:respawn:/bin/login -f pi tty1 </dev/tty1 >/dev/tty1 2>&1

- change /etc/rc.local, add the following lines before the exit 0 line

        #
        # run mu-photos
        #
        cd /home/pi/mu-photos
        bash run2.sh
- install the software on a folder /home/pi/mu-photos



DEPENDENCIES
============
- fbi

